{
  "text": "Since the majority of our data involves adoptive transfer of purified transgenic T cells into immunedeficient mice, it is of interest to consider whether antigenic drift can occur in a normal tumor-bearing host in which the immune response consists of CD4 T cells, CD8 T cells, and B cells. Since we have verified our conclusion with adoptively transferred total spleen cells from TCR \u03b1 chain-transgenic mice that have all subsets of lymphocytes, we believe antigenic drift can happen in a host with multiple subsets of lymphocytes. Moreover, recent studies indicate that homeostatic proliferation of T cells, upon adoptive transfer to an immune-deficient host, may enhance the efficacy of immune therapy both in experimental animals [CITATION_1] and in humans [CITATION_2] . Such a setting is essentially identical to the approach in the current study.",
